This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a visual SLAM system based on photometric bundle adjustment. It may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as SLAM is a common problem in robotics. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for improving the accuracy of the system, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with 3D reconstruction from video.
